## 9. Mapping LLM Search Params to OpenSearch Filters

The LLM returns semantic values like `"gender": "men"`. These need mapping to the existing OpenSearch filter format:

```
LLM gender "men" --> product_type filter: ["Unisex"] (matching GENDER_PRODUCT_TYPE_MAP)
LLM gender "women" --> product_type filter: ["Women's"]
LLM gender "youth" --> product_type filter: ["Youth"]
LLM gender "unisex" --> no filter (all types)

LLM priceLevel "budget" --> price_level boost: [1]
LLM priceLevel "midrange" --> price_level boost: [2]
LLM priceLevel "premium" --> price_level boost: [3]
```

This mapping should be a private method in `ConversationalSearchService` that takes `IIntentSearchParams` and returns filter/boost arrays compatible with the existing `searchProducts` query structure.

